08/10/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias met with Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat on Wednesday (October 7th), as part of phase two of talks aimed at reunifying the divided island. 
UN Special Envoy for Cyprus Alexander Downer also attended and said afterwards that this round focused on governance and distribution of powers. 
He described the meeting as friendly. 
A neck problem forced Christofias to cancel Thursday's planned talks. 
(Financial Mirror - 08/10/09; CNN Turk, Anadolu news agency - 07/10/09)
